00:00:07,240 --> 00:02:12,298
Tokuma Shoten, Nippon Television, Hakuhodo present Only Yesterday Executive Producers Yasuyoshi TOKUMA Yoshio SASAKI and Ritsuo ISOBE Based on "Omoide Poroporo" by Hotaru OKAMOTO and Yuko TONE Voices Miki IMAI Toshiro YANAGIBA Yoko HONNA Music by Masaru HOSHI Theme song performed by Harumi MIYAKO Producer Toshio SUZUKI General Producer Hayao MIYAZAKI Screenplay written & directed by Isao TAKAHATA With ten days off, I figured you'd go abroad.

2
00:02:12,398 --> 00:02:15,094
But you're off to Yamagata, right?

3
00:02:15,201 --> 00:02:16,190
Yes.

4
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,532
Broke up with your boyfriend?

5
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:21,465
I just prefer the countryside.

6
00:02:21,584 --> 00:02:22,178
- See ya!

7
00:02:22,198 --> 00:02:22,792
- Bye!

8
00:02:23,209 --> 00:02:24,267
Let's go play!

9
00:02:24,377 --> 00:02:25,935
Bye now!

10
00:02:26,045 --> 00:02:27,774
Later!

11
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,248
Did you get good grades?

12
00:02:30,426 --> 00:02:31,919
No.

13
00:02:31,939 --> 00:02:33,432
But I don't care.

14
00:02:33,553 --> 00:02:34,383
How come?

15
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:37,650
As soon as I get home, we're traveling to Grandma's.

16
00:02:37,757 --> 00:02:40,055
So I won't get yelled at for ages.

17
00:02:40,170 --> 00:02:41,731
Lucky you!

18
00:02:41,751 --> 00:02:43,312
Are you going away too?

19
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:44,869
Yeah, to Nagano.

20
00:02:44,889 --> 00:02:46,319
How about you, Taeko?

21
00:02:46,432 --> 00:02:47,330
I'm not sure.

22
00:02:47,634 --> 00:02:50,068
My Dad bought a summer place.

23
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:51,828
Wow... that's great!

24
00:02:53,773 --> 00:02:56,708
Such a bad grade in math again.

25
00:02:57,410 --> 00:03:00,311
But I got a "B" in science.

26
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:03,340
Are we going away for the holidays?

27
00:03:03,449 --> 00:03:04,882
Not really.

28
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,619
Take me someplace.

29
00:03:08,231 --> 00:03:10,441
I'll take you to a movie.

30
00:03:10,461 --> 00:03:12,671
Find out what's playing.

31
00:03:12,802 --> 00:03:14,295
Not that.

32
00:03:14,315 --> 00:03:15,808
I mean to the country...

33
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:16,827
The country?

34
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:19,296
Like Grandma's country house.

35
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:20,889
Grandma lives with us.

36
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,173
- Grandpa's then...

37
00:03:22,193 --> 00:03:23,356
- He's dead.

38
00:03:23,469 --> 00:03:27,565
We don't have relatives in the country, so don't ask.

39
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:35,613
My family had lived in Tokyo for generations.

40
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:38,775
I envied friends who had family in the countryside.

41
00:03:41,798 --> 00:03:43,308
It's too late to book.

42
00:03:43,328 --> 00:03:44,838
All hotels will be full.

43
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:47,156
But I really want to go...

44
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:49,589
What about "Onoya"?

45
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:51,800
We're regulars.

46
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:53,848
They'd have a room for us.

47
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:55,127
Where's that?

48
00:03:55,245 --> 00:03:56,954
Good idea.

49
00:03:56,974 --> 00:03:58,683
Taeko's never been there.

50
00:03:58,805 --> 00:03:59,965
That's right.

51
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:02,837
Is it in the mountains... by the sea?

52
00:04:03,209 --> 00:04:04,836
It's in Atami.

53
00:04:06,045 --> 00:04:07,069
Atami?

54
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:09,808
You get to ride the bullet train.

55
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,907
Sure, you ll love it.

56
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:16,679
Atami...

57
00:04:16,789 --> 00:04:19,553
Lots of different hot springs...

58
00:04:19,792 --> 00:04:22,886
There's a huge Roman Bath.

59
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:28,798
And others, like the Swan Bath and the Violet Bath.

60
00:04:28,901 --> 00:04:30,698
The beautiful Violet Bath!

61
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:33,032
The Violet Bath...

62
00:04:33,182 --> 00:04:34,294
Oh yes.

63
00:04:34,314 --> 00:04:35,426
It's fantastic.

64
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,372
You love hot springs, right?

65
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:41,843
Since father's working, you four go.

66
00:04:42,248 --> 00:04:43,340
What?!

67
00:04:46,919 --> 00:04:48,250
Us?

68
00:04:48,354 --> 00:04:49,787
Go too?!

69
00:04:56,529 --> 00:05:00,363
I'm amazed you show up every morning.

70
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:03,162
Everyone else has left town.

71
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:07,768
Aren't you going anywhere?

72
00:05:08,084 --> 00:05:08,764
- Yes, I am.

73
00:05:08,784 --> 00:05:09,464
- Where?

74
00:05:09,575 --> 00:05:10,633
Atami.

75
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,464
Atami?

76
00:05:12,484 --> 00:05:14,028
What's in Atami?

77
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,944
Hot springs.

78
00:05:19,852 --> 00:05:21,376
It's good timing.

79
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:25,480
We're going away next week.

80
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:29,150
No-one will be around for ages.

81
00:05:31,941 --> 00:05:32,853
Hello.

82
00:05:32,873 --> 00:05:33,785
Okajima residence.

83
00:05:33,910 --> 00:05:35,289
Nanako?

84
00:05:35,309 --> 00:05:36,688
It's Taeko.

85
00:05:36,813 --> 00:05:39,040
I leave today.

86
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:41,287
Any message for your husband's family?

87
00:05:41,851 --> 00:05:44,061
Not really.

88
00:05:44,081 --> 00:05:46,291
Just buy them something.

89
00:05:46,412 --> 00:05:49,245
Say it's from us and I'll pay you back.

90
00:05:49,359 --> 00:05:51,057
Don't worry about it.

91
00:05:51,077 --> 00:05:52,775
How's Mom?

92
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:54,409
She's out today.

93
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:58,887
She was mad you turned down that guy's proposal.

94
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:02,856
"At 27, that's the best offer she's going to get!"

95
00:06:02,962 --> 00:06:05,556
It's all she talks about.

96
00:06:05,675 --> 00:06:07,589
She's got a point.

97
00:06:07,609 --> 00:06:09,523
You're not young anymore...

98
00:06:09,635 --> 00:06:10,829
Oh, yeah?

99
00:06:10,937 --> 00:06:12,427
Definitely.

100
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,938
You've got to settle down eventually.

101
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:19,535
By the way, did you really work in the fields last year?

102
00:06:19,655 --> 00:06:21,466
Yes, harvesting rice.

103
00:06:21,486 --> 00:06:23,297
This year, I'm picking safflower.

104
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,440
Safflower?

105
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:28,577
Thanks to you, I finally have family in the countryside.

106
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:32,157
So, I'm making the most of it!

107
00:06:33,459 --> 00:06:35,256
Give me a break!

108
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:43,191
Rather than stay in that old house, why not treat yourself to a fancy hotel for once?

109
00:06:43,302 --> 00:06:45,395
Maybe you'd meet a nice boy.

110
00:06:45,648 --> 00:06:47,875
No way.

111
00:06:47,895 --> 00:06:50,122
You mean a hotel like "Onoya"?

112
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,642
"Onoya"?

113
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,872
Not that again!

114
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:59,150
You've got to get over it.

115
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:02,312
Let go of that baggage from the past!

116
00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:16,693
My sisters, of course, would never go to a place like atami.

117
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:20,669
Grandma...

118
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:23,571
Almost done?

119
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:26,341
Let's go to another bath.

120
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,846
We just went.

121
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:31,576
Only to the Swan Bath.

122
00:07:33,719 --> 00:07:44,960
Bored to tears, I went alone to the Brothers Grimm Bath the Mermaid Bath, the Lemon Bath, and the Violet Bath, one after the other.

123
00:07:45,064 --> 00:07:47,089
It's enormous!

124
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:51,125
When I got to the Roman Bath, my head was spinning.

125
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:54,831
It's amazing...

126
00:08:04,851 --> 00:08:06,546
And I fainted.

127
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:10,116
And with that, my trip was over.

128
00:08:10,223 --> 00:08:13,989
Followed by endless weeks of vacation.

129
00:08:28,107 --> 00:08:33,704
The other day, my sisters and I were reminiscing.

130
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:42,048
We couldn't stop laughing as the memories came flooding back.

131
00:08:46,993 --> 00:08:48,153
Had one before?

132
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:49,956
No, it's my first time.

133
00:08:50,396 --> 00:08:52,091
I'm the one who asked for it.

134
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,426
Yeah, we know.

135
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,797
Where did you buy it?

136
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,267
Senbikiya in Ginza.

137
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,837
Must have been expensive.

138
00:09:00,339 --> 00:09:02,034
How do we eat it?

139
00:09:02,141 --> 00:09:03,369
Slice it into rings.

140
00:09:03,476 --> 00:09:04,943
But how?

141
00:09:06,946 --> 00:09:08,379
I don't know.

142
00:09:09,615 --> 00:09:12,778
Didn't you ask in the store?

143
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:19,782
We'll eat it next Sunday.

144
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,292
Why not now?!

145
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:24,953
We don't know how.

146
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,632
I'll have a banana.

147
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,362
Me too.

148
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:39,174
Strange fruit they have in those hot countries.

149
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,481
I'm home!

150
00:09:43,849 --> 00:09:45,817
I know how to eat the pineapple!

151
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,215
Really?

152
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:53,390
I'll take that.

153
00:09:54,126 --> 00:09:55,423
Mind your fingers.

154
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:57,826
Wouldn't a carving knife be best?

155
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:13,001
What a nice smell.

156
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,313
It smells so good.

157
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:28,191
I see.

158
00:10:29,271 --> 00:10:29,996
Get plates.

159
00:10:30,016 --> 00:10:30,741
Quick.

160
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:33,127
Okay.

161
00:10:34,934 --> 00:10:36,196
Let us eat.

162
00:10:57,923 --> 00:10:59,686
It's hard.

163
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:05,725
It's not very good.

164
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,389
Not so sweet.

165
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,559
Nothing like the canned stuff.

166
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:13,503
Live long enough and you see lots of different things.

167
00:11:18,821 --> 00:11:19,967
- You can have mine.

168
00:11:19,987 --> 00:11:21,133
- Mine too.

169
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,573
It's delicious...

170
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:00,348
Don't force yourself.

171
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:02,045
You'll get a stomachache.

172
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:14,263
What a let down.

173
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:19,132
Bananas taste much better.

174
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:20,466
You're so right.

175
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:23,701
Bananas are still the king of fruits.

176
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:25,071
I ll have one now.

177
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:55,503
The king of fruit is...

178
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:57,872
the banana, after all.

179
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:07,848
The year I fainted at the baths and had my first pineapple...

180
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:15,625
the Beatles came to Japan, started the rock 'n'roll band and electric guitar craze.

181
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:23,931
My sister Nanako, a freshman in art school, was up on all the trends.

182
00:13:24,703 --> 00:13:27,103
Yeah, the Beatles'lyrics are great.

183
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:34,908
When she wore a mini-skirt, she'd cover her bottom going up the stairs.

184
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:43,313
My clever sister, Yaeko, was crazy about some Takarazuka actress.

185
00:13:43,422 --> 00:13:44,753
Yaeko...

186
00:13:46,091 --> 00:13:47,786
I told you to knock!

187
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:57,467
My sisters' memories are mainly of fashion and pop trends.

188
00:13:57,870 --> 00:14:02,830
For them, 1966 is the height of nostalgia.

189
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,770
Whereas I was only ten years old.

190
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:11,546
My favorite band had yet to debut....

191
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:16,280
My only memories are the back and forth between school and home.

192
00:14:16,388 --> 00:14:18,356
...mine was pinned on the wall!

193
00:14:18,457 --> 00:14:20,618
That's nice.

194
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:25,095
And it might be entered in an essay contest.

195
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:27,791
So, teacher kept it.

196
00:14:28,277 --> 00:14:29,957
- I'd be so happy...

197
00:14:29,977 --> 00:14:31,657
- You didn't finish lunch again.

198
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:34,836
Why do you hide the pickles inside the bread?

199
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,840
'Cause I hate them.

200
00:14:36,952 --> 00:14:38,730
I've got to throw it away.

201
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,528
What a waste.

202
00:14:41,247 --> 00:14:43,112
Such a picky eater!

203
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:50,115
I'd rather you were a good eater than a good essay writer.

204
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:09,839
How can you drink that stuff?

205
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:13,351
Milk's okay.

206
00:15:13,371 --> 00:15:15,302
It's onions I hate.

207
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:19,077
I'm leaving carrots so I've got no choice.

208
00:15:19,952 --> 00:15:24,514
Who decided we can only leave one thing?

209
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:25,749
Shall I drink it?

210
00:15:25,858 --> 00:15:27,086
Would you?

211
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:30,418
You'll eat my onions next time?

212
00:15:42,885 --> 00:15:44,014
- Carrots?

213
00:15:44,034 --> 00:15:45,163
- We're allowed one thing!

214
00:15:54,553 --> 00:15:56,418
Two bowls is gross.

215
00:15:57,356 --> 00:15:59,847
People who run in the corridor...

216
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:05,056
...when the hall monitor says stop, should be punished.

217
00:16:05,531 --> 00:16:08,591
How are you gonna do that?

218
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:10,566
They shouldn't do it.

219
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:11,861
That's right.

220
00:16:12,037 --> 00:16:13,937
You might bump into someone.

221
00:16:14,039 --> 00:16:18,373
If I bumped into you I'd bounce a mile!

222
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:19,603
Get lost!

223
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:24,176
Running is no big deal.

224
00:16:24,283 --> 00:16:25,375
I agree!

225
00:16:25,594 --> 00:16:27,274
- Let's change the rule.

226
00:16:27,294 --> 00:16:28,974
- But we already decided.

227
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:31,713
Raise your hand if you want to speak.

228
00:16:32,267 --> 00:16:33,259
- Here!

229
00:16:33,279 --> 00:16:34,271
- Miss Tani.

230
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:42,457
The hall monitor should chase the offender, catch them and punish them.

231
00:16:43,946 --> 00:16:44,626
Mr.

232
00:16:44,646 --> 00:16:45,326
Suzuki.

233
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:50,236
Then the hall monitor should be punished for running too.

234
00:16:50,352 --> 00:16:51,049
He's right!

235
00:16:51,069 --> 00:16:51,766
He's right!

236
00:16:52,244 --> 00:16:53,734
Way to go!

237
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:54,913
He's right.

238
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:57,004
Miss Tani.

239
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:02,380
The hall monitor shouldn't be punished because...

240
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:08,019
...it's like a policeman chasing a speeding car.

241
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,494
Any objections?

242
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:20,131
It makes sense...

243
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:21,968
No more running.

244
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:27,878
So, the hall monitor can chase offenders.

245
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:31,482
Any other issues?

246
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:34,117
Miss Tani.

247
00:17:34,797 --> 00:17:35,539
- Her again.

248
00:17:35,559 --> 00:17:36,301
- Busybody.

249
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:37,753
Be quiet.

250
00:17:37,856 --> 00:17:40,256
Some people don't finish lunch.

251
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:45,457
I just read an article on the Vietnam War.

252
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:49,427
There are many unfortunate people overseas.

253
00:17:49,535 --> 00:17:51,093
We're very lucky.

254
00:17:51,203 --> 00:17:53,103
Lucky to have you near me!

255
00:17:56,308 --> 00:17:59,744
We should be grateful for our food.

256
00:17:59,845 --> 00:18:06,583
We're allowed to leave one thing on our plates, but I think it's wrong!

257
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:11,952
Goody two-shoes.

258
00:18:12,401 --> 00:18:14,611
- It can't hurt to leave one thing.

259
00:18:14,631 --> 00:18:16,841
- Let's all leave milk...

260
00:18:16,972 --> 00:18:18,533
- Give it to someone else...

261
00:18:18,553 --> 00:18:20,114
- Of course.

262
00:18:20,242 --> 00:18:22,270
- People hide leftovers in bread.

263
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:24,318
- That's cheating!

264
00:18:24,536 --> 00:18:26,470
I hate school food.

265
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:29,273
If you want to speak, raise your hand!

266
00:18:30,042 --> 00:18:32,533
What a revolting situation.

267
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:47,714
That night in bed, after chatting to my sisters more memories from fifth grade came rushing back.

268
00:18:50,772 --> 00:18:53,084
Our pet dog... .

269
00:18:53,104 --> 00:18:55,416
School sports day...

270
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:58,862
being scared by gross horror comics....

271
00:19:00,239 --> 00:19:02,901
longing for an electric pencil-sharpener...

272
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:08,737
So many little details, one after the other...

273
00:19:09,214 --> 00:19:16,310
playing in my head like a movie, almost overpowering me.

274
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,084
Is there a Miss Okajima here?

275
00:19:24,763 --> 00:19:25,752
That's her.

276
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:41,040
Hirota in our class says he likes you.

